opening_comment: Moved from OSB ID743628:  This maritime boundary is tagged 'robot 200nm', but it's the 24NM contiguous zone boundary [dandv, 2013-07-15 11:19:54 CEST]
the administrative boundaries in this area are very complex, they should be simplified

Chile has straight baselines: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Baselines_chile.png and http://www.state.gov/documents/organization/61366.pdf So, the OSM territorial waters & contiguous zone, which follow the coastline, are wrong.
